                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode2/invalid-json-api-problem.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>The nice API Problem JSON format always has a <code>type</code> key, so let's at least start
looking for that in the response. Use <code>$this-&gt;asserter()-&gt;assertResponsePropertyEquals()</code>
and pass it the <code>$response</code> and <code>type</code> as the key. For the value - how about
<code>invalid_body_format</code>. That's our <em>second</em> special error "type" - the first was
<code>validation_error</code>.</p>
