<p>This should get our test to fail again:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/phpunit -c app --filter testInvalidJson</div></code></pre>
<p>Gooood - we're still returning the exception HTML.</p>
<h2 id="creating-the-apiproblem">Creating the ApiProblem <a class="headerlink" href="invalid-json-api-problem#creating-the-apiproblem" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Let's fix this just like we did for validation errors: by creating an <code>ApiProblem</code>
object. First, we need a new <code>type</code> constant. Create a second constant called
<code>TYPE_INVALID_REQUEST_BODY_FORMAT</code> and set that to the string from our test: <code>invalid_body_format</code>.
Setup a title for this too: how about "Invalid JSON format sent". And I better fix
my syntax error:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="af7772f9e6">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-60" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            60 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="src/AppBundle/Api/ApiProblem.php">src/AppBundle/Api/ApiProblem.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
