<h2 id="we-re-stuck">We're stuck <a class="headerlink" href="invalid-json-api-problem#we-re-stuck" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Gosh, everything is going really well! And now we're stuck. For validation, we took
the <code>ApiProblem</code>, turned it into a Response and returned it. But inside <code>processForm()</code>,
we're big trouble: the return value of this method isn't being used. We can
only <em>throw</em> an exception to stop the flow. And while we <em>can</em> control the status
code of an exception, the response body that an <code>HttpException</code> generates is still
an HTML error page.</p>

    
                        </div>
                    </div>
